TA-elasticsearch-to-Splunk Edge Processor OR Splunk ES/Cloud
------------------------------------------------------------

Modular input to pull logs from Elasticsearch using REST API and forward them to Splunk Edge Processor/ Splunk Cloud or ES via HTTP Event Collector (HEC).

Setup:
1. Install the app on your Splunk Heavy Forwarder.
	a) Copy the .zip to your Splunk Heavy Forwarder.
	b) Extract it under: $SPLUNK_HOME/etc/apps/
	c) For example: unzip TA-elasticsearch-to-edge.zip -d $SPLUNK_HOME/etc/apps/
	d) Restart Splunk: $SPLUNK_HOME/bin/splunk restart

2. Use the UI or inputs.conf to configure the connection.
	a) Configure the Modular Input via Splunk UI
	b) Go to Settings > Data Inputs > Elasticsearch to Edge Processor
	c) Add a new input using the UI form powered by setup.xml
	d) Define values for each environment (e.g., prod,staging in the environment field)
	e) Validate Data Flow -> Check logs in $SPLUNK_HOME/var/log/splunk/ta-elasticsearch-to-edge.log
	f) Confirm data reaches Edge Processor via HEC
	
3. The App upports multi-environment fetch, persistent timestamp tracking, retry logic, TLS, and proxy configs.

